tool.name: CulturalES

param.name: in_aoi
param.dialogReference:
Draw an area of interest to extract Flickr photo densities for the selected ecosystem service type.

NOTE: larger areas may result in very long execution time and/or potential errors.
param.pythonReference:
Draw an area of interest to extract Flickr photo densities for the selected ecosystem service type.

NOTE: larger areas may result in very long execution time and/or potential errors.

param.name: in_es_type
param.dialogReference:
Select the desired ecosystem service type. Default: Nature.

NOTE: in this version of the tool, only Nature is available as an option.
param.pythonReference:
Select the desired ecosystem service type. Default: Nature.

NOTE: in this version of the tool, only Nature is available as an option.

param.name: in_n_photos
param.dialogReference:
Type a number between 0 and 1 to represent the fraction of extracted photos that will be used to predict the selected ecosystem service type.

NOTE: lower numbers generally speed up the execution time of the tool.
param.pythonReference:
Type a number between 0 and 1 to represent the fraction of extracted photos that will be used to predict the selected ecosystem service type.

NOTE: lower numbers generally speed up the execution time of the tool.

param.name: in_start_year
param.dialogReference:
Type the starting year to be used when selecting Flickr photos from the database.

NOTE: This number has to be between 2005-2017.
param.pythonReference:
Type the starting year to be used when selecting Flickr photos from the database.

NOTE: This number has to be between 2005-2017.

param.name: in_end_year
param.dialogReference:
Type the ending year to be used when selecting Flickr photos from the database.

NOTE: This number has to be between 2005-2017. Also, it cannot be smaller than the starting year.
param.pythonReference:
Type the ending year to be used when selecting Flickr photos from the database.

NOTE: This number has to be between 2005-2017. Also, it cannot be smaller than the starting year.

param.name: in_prob_threshold
param.dialogReference:
Type a number between 0 and 1 (default 0.5) to be used a probability threshold when classifying Flickr photos to the selected ecosystem service type.

NOTE: a higher number implies a result that only maps photos that were classified with high confidence. Lower numbers imply that you accept a higher risk of incorrectly classifying photos.
param.pythonReference:
Type a number between 0 and 1 (default 0.5) to be used a probability threshold when classifying Flickr photos to the selected ecosystem service type.

NOTE: a higher number implies a result that only maps photos that were classified with high confidence. Lower numbers imply that you accept a higher risk of incorrectly classifying photos.

param.name: in_grid_type
param.dialogReference: Select the desired grid type to be used when calculating the photo densities for each grid cell.
param.pythonReference: Select the desired grid type to be used when calculating the photo densities for each grid cell.

param.name: in_cell_size
param.dialogReference:
Select the desired spatial resolution of the grid cells to be used when calculating the photo densities for each grid cell. You can leave this blank and the tool will automatically calculate a resolution for you.

NOTE: a higher number (coarser resolution) will result in greater aggregation of photo densities. The resolution units MUST be expressed in decimal degrees and fractions of decimal degrees.
param.pythonReference:
Select the desired spatial resolution of the grid cells to be used when calculating the photo densities for each grid cell. You can leave this blank and the tool will automatically calculate a resolution for you.

NOTE: a higher number (coarser resolution) will result in greater aggregation of photo densities. The resolution units MUST be expressed in decimal degrees and fractions of decimal degrees.

param.name: out_features
param.dialogReference: The name and disk location of the output feature class that represents gridded photo densities for the selected ecosystem service type.
param.pythonReference: The name and disk location of the output feature class that represents gridded photo densities for the selected ecosystem service type.

tool.summary: The non-material benefits people obtain from ecosystems are called ‘cultural services'. They include aesthetic inspiration, cultural identity, sense of home, and spiritual experience related to the natural environment. Typically, opportunities for tourism and for recreation are also considered within the group. Cultural services are deeply interconnected with each other and often connected to provisioning and regulating services: Small scale fishing is not only about food and income, but also about fishers’ way of life. In many situations, cultural services are among the most important values people associate with Nature – it is therefore critical to understand them. Our tool helps users understand which areas have the highest concentration of cultural ecosystem services or the non-material benefits of Nature and therefore identify locations of high recreational, inspiration, aesthetics and spiritual value.
